<h1>Welcome to the University Club!</h1>
<p>Located on campus in Pembina Hall, the University Club&#8217;s reputation is matched only by the view from its patio doors &#8212; the enchanting shoreline of the Historic Red River.</p>
<p>Its purpose is to facilitate and enhance the missions and activities of the University community.  It provides a common, informal gathering place, a place for broad community interaction, rooms for social &amp; business meetings &amp; facilities for dining, receptions &amp; meetings.</p>
<div id="main_image"></div>
<p>The Club is open to its members &amp; their guests for lunch &amp; bar service.  In addition, it features a wide variety of special events &amp; may be reserved for private use.</p>
<p>We invite you to relax in our informal surroundings, sample our superior cuisine featuring our internationally renowned Executive Chef &amp; let yourself experience the diferrence.</p>
<h2>Dining at The Club</h2>
<p>From casual dining to social affairs, the concenial &amp; convenient University Club provides a variety of hospitality services.</p>
<h2>The Centennial Room</h2>
<p>The perfect setting for quiet a la carte dining during lunch.  The luncheon menu offers a variety of salads, sandwiches, hot entrees &amp; two daily specials.  The Centennial Room also accomodates private luncheons, receptions, dinner parties &amp; meetings.  Lunch is served Monday through Friday, 11:30am &#8211; 2:00pm.  Reservations are not necessary, but to avoid disappointment call 474-9480.</p>
<h2>The Main Dining Room</h2>
<p>For relaxed &amp; casual dining, experience our buffet-style lunch.  On our various serving lines we offer a sandwich station, salad bar, soup station, hot luncheon buffet, baked goods, dessert bar, coffee station &amp; bar service.  The dining room also opens onto the patio where we feature barbecues during the spring &amp; summer months.  The dining room may also be reserved for a range of social gatherings.  Lunch is served daily from 11:30am &#8211; 2:00pm.</p>
<h2>Dinner Service</h2>
<p>Dinner service is available every Friday night from 5:00pm &#8211; 8:00pm, with a variety of Specials offered.  Monday to Thursday dinner reservations will be accepted for six or more people with advance notice.</p>
<p>The Club offers an array of special events to enjoy throughout the year, including Thanksgiving, American Thanksgiving, Holiday Luncheon Buffets, New Year&#8217;s Eve, Chinese New Year, St.Patrick&#8217;s Day, Easter &amp; Mother&#8217;s Day, etc.</p>
<h2>Reserving The Club</h2>
<p>For many years the Club has provided more than just a place to dine.  Our long tradition of hospitality &amp; campus location make it the ideal setting for hosting receptions for visiting scholars, departmental gatherings, weddings, anniversaries, graduations, luncheons, dinners, cocktail parties &amp; many other functions.  We have the ability to meet parties from 15 to 200 guests, with ample parking available in D lot during evenings and weekends all day.</p>
<p>Reserving the Club is as easy as picking up the phone.  For catering information regarding availability of space and for advice in planning special events, contact the Club at 474-9480.</p>
            
